+# Hardening Wave 3 — Production Boundary Closure
+
+Date: 2026-06-19
+
+## Goal
+
+Continue the production-readiness work by closing the remaining long-tail request-validation and queue-ingress gaps without changing the product architecture.
+
+## Scope
+
+This wave focused on routes that still accepted loosely parsed request bodies or query parameters:
+
+- `apps/api/src/routes/jobs.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/routes/signals.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/routes/outcomes.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/routes/ingest.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/routes/prospects.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/routes/packs.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/routes/auth.ts`
+- `apps/api/src/lib/validate.ts`
+
+## Changes
+
+### Central validation helpers
+
+`apps/api/src/lib/validate.ts`
+
+- Added `formatZodError()`
+- Added `parseBody()`
+- Added `parseQuery()`
+- Added `validateQuery()`
+- Added shared optional ID parsing
+- Added query integer coercion helper
+
+This lets routes validate ad hoc payloads without forcing every endpoint into middleware form.
+
+### Jobs route hardening
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/jobs.ts`
+
+- Added Zod schemas for single-lead AI jobs.
+- Added Zod schema for reply-analysis jobs.
+- Added Zod schema for bulk research jobs.
+- Validated queue names and job IDs before job lookup.
+- Preserved the mandatory billable scope for reply analysis.
+- Fixed bulk research response mapping so `leadId` is sourced from job data instead of the BullMQ job name.
+
+### Signals route hardening
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/signals.ts`
+
+- Added strict query validation for list filters.
+- Added strict body validation for manual signal creation.
+- Restricted signal type to known signal types.
+- Enforced signal strength/source reliability/industry relevance ranges.
+- Added safe parsing for dates, URLs, and evidence confidence.
+- Prevented malformed evidence from reaching persistence.
+
+### Outcomes route hardening
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/outcomes.ts`
+
+- Added strict body validation for outcome recording.
+- Fixed a correctness risk where string values like `"false"` could previously be recorded as `true` through `Boolean(...)`.
+- Added strict model-reset body validation.
+- Preserved the dual authentication model: ingest API key or user JWT.
+
+### Ingest route hardening
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/ingest.ts`
+
+- Added strict batch-body validation.
+- Enforced batch cap at schema level.
+- Enforced email syntax before lead creation.
+- Normalized emails at the boundary.
+- Validated source tags, campaign IDs, and scoring inputs.
+- Added query validation for ingest API key rotation/deletion.
+
+### Prospects route hardening
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/prospects.ts`
+
+- Added schema validation for prospect CSV import request envelopes.
+- Added schema validation for signal import request envelopes.
+- Added bounded row parsing for imported text fields.
+- Added non-negative numeric validation for imported employee/revenue/deal-value fields.
+- Added signal import validation for dates, strength, and confidence.
+- Added strict optional body validation for outreach-intent approval and materialization.
+
+### Packs and auth hardening
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/packs.ts`
+
+- Added schema validation for pack application.
+
+`apps/api/src/routes/auth.ts`
+
+- Added schema validation for profile updates.
+- Enforced paired `currentPassword` + `newPassword` for password changes.
